<title>Traffic</title>

<section>
	<title>Introduction</title>
	<para>
		<libraryname>Traffic</libraryname> is a software system used for teaching introductory programming. It consists of a library - the <projectname>Traffic library</projectname> - and several example applications that use the <projectname>Traffic library</projectname>: <projectname>Flathunt</projectname>,<projectname>City3D</projectname>, <projectname>CityTime</projectname>, and the <projectname>Touch</projectname> applications accompanying the textbook <projectname>A Touch of Class</projectname>. The goal of <projectname>Traffic</projectname> is to make learning to program exciting, interesting and realistic.
	</para>
</section>

